Lesson 1.2 Exiting VIM  
1.press <ESC> to enter normal mode.  
2.type: :q!<Enter>;discarding any change 

Lesson 1.3 TEXT EDITING - DELETION
1.move the cursor on top of character to be deleted.
2.press the x key

Lesson 1.4 TEXT EDITING - INSERTION
1.move the cursor on top of the character BEFORE which the text is to be inserted.
2.press i and type in the necessary additions.

Lesson 1.5 TEXT EDITING - APPEDING
1.Press A and type in the necessary additions.
